&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary/Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will support the NFL’s departmental leads (three Senior Vice Presidents) with a focus on daily administrative and core operational support across these core functions of the League, in order to drive efficiency and optimize the productivity of these teams and leaders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Administrative Support:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and schedule meetings and conference calls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manager calendars across different time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and distribute agendas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer and route telephone calls and incoming mail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arrange and manage travel schedules and travel expenses&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and process P-Card transactions and expenses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare meeting materials and presentations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create templates for letters and memos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and maintain department inventory and materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations Support:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing of invoices, setting up new vendors and other financial system operations on behalf of the department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating templated agreements and routing contracts through Docusign and other systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing staffing and credential needs for events and meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and issue correspondence to key partners, NFL clubs, vendors, and fan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with key leaders across the three departments Corporate Social Responsibility, Football Communications, and Human Resources.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree from a Four-Year College or University Preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;One to Two Years Related in Sports-related or Media Industry, preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General knowledge and/or interest in the National Football League strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Key Attributes / Characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong ability to multi-task and manage multiple people and functions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have exceptional prioritizing, organizational, communication, initiative, judgment and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated and strong work ethic and integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer proficient in Microsoft Office (PowerPoint Skills a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to maintain the highest level of confidentiality&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Terms / Expected Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job posting is for a position with one of the NFL’s third-party agency partners that provides services to the NFL. The individual selected for this role will be an employee of that third-party agency and not the NFL. All compensation, benefits, and other terms and conditions of employme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
