&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview /Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NFL Films Archival department seeks a responsible and organized individual, with an interest and knowledge in film.&amp;nbsp; The responsibilities will include but are not limited to research and restoration of our archives.&amp;nbsp; Film Vault maintenance and organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and restoration of our film for archival purposes or producer requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data entry in our film system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning and utilizing the Neg Log database to identify and restore shots to original camera rolls for the purpose of scanning and archiving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The employee will be expected to learn how to use our film cleaning system. This includes keeping film organized as it moves through the cleaning process, along with recognizing if the machines are not running properly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;They will be responsible for returning film to its location in the film vault, along with reorganizing and updating locations as we move through the archival project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The employee will also be expected to have a level of flexibility. The projects we work on are ever evolving and our employees’ ability to evolve with updated priorities is very important.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of Word and Excel is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail when entering film data into our system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A general understanding of film handling techniques. On the job training will be provided with the expectation that the techniques learned will be utilized at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
