&lt;p&gt;The Associate Director will, subject to the supervision of the executive producer, producer and/or director assigned to the program, perform the following functions, or supervise the performance of them by others, on programs to which he or she is assigned. This person will work weekly on NFL Media shows as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Essential Functions:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confer with the producer and/or the director on plans for the program and attend production meetings concerning the program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time master control to commercial break; time the program back from commercial break; communicate timing of all taped elements of the program. Will also communicate throughout the show with any other production partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate production tasks with the stage manager, all production and technical personnel, including but not limited to audio, TD, graphics, lighting and graphics operators or their producers, as well as other Associate Directors and other employees of the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mark the show rundown in ENPS, including music cues, sound effects, TD effects, remotes, tape times and more. The Associate Director works with show personnel – including producers – to execute pre-production and live production of the show.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work across departments (graphics, file transfer, edit coordinators), to ensure timely delivery of all show elements. The AD is responsible for knowing the correct sponsorships and billboards for their show and works with appropriate parties to make sure assets air correctly. They will assist in coordinating and timing all sponsored elements for their shows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with playback and EVS operators on all tape elements during show production. This includes previewing all playbacks for the show they are assigned as well as ensuring all pre-taped segments are recorded. Will also work with TOC on preparing remotes involved in production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NFL knowledge is essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Preferred Experience:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 3 years working in a live studio environment, preferably sports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DGA preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of ENPS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Other Key Attributes / Characteristics:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and passion for professional sports, especially NFL football&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure in a live control room&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrives in a collaborative environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Supervisory Responsibility:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This position will be responsible for the following:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates with audio &amp;amp; music department on commercial tracks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Will be a point of contact for all Encompass (Master Control) communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Physical Demands:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekends and some late/early hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasionally will need to sit for long periods of time while on-air for a live show.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Travel:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unlikely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Expected Hours of Work:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8-10 hours per day, sometimes more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7-month seasonal employment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Salary / Pay Range&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;job-details__description-content basic-formatter&quot; data-bind=&quot;html: pageData().job.description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NFL Digital Media team is seeking a Seasonal Part-Time Digital Content Desk Assistant who is tasked with assisting the NFL Media Assignment Desk in all phases of the newsgathering process for digital content. This role requires working with others at various levels on the assignment desk.&amp;nbsp; The role will work closely with NFL.com editorial staff as well as ticker operators and content producers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Potential candidates must meet the following criteria and perform the following duties:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to follow instructions and work well with others in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task and prioritize daily assignments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate strong communication skills both verbally and written&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to meet deadlines under pressure situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong football knowledge and&amp;nbsp;awareness of NFL events and stories, ability to quickly identify players and coaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with utilizing social media for content gathering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with proactive outreach via phone, social media or email&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in copy-editing preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Premiere or Adobe a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Tagboard a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be flexible with work schedule including weekends and holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Education and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-year degree or equivalent education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years in a newsroom or journalism environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Education and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous professional experience in TV Production environment is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Key Attributes / Characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have strong editorial skills and NFL knowledge to know what video and soundbites are best to edit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to respond quickly on short deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to respond positively to criticism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team attitude is mandatory in all tasks requested from the smallest to largest&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Terms / Expected Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;30 hours or less a week over at 7-month period&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May include weekend shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Part-time, non-exempt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is an in-office position – no remote work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary / Pay Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job posting contains a pay range, which represents the range of salaries or hourly rates that the NFL believes, in good faith, at the time of this posting that it might be willing to pay for the posted job in the location(s) specified. The NFL expects to hire for this position near the middle of the range. Only in truly rare and exceptional circumstances, where an external candidate has experience, credentials or expertise that far exceed those required or expected for the position, would the NFL consider paying a salary or rate near the higher end of the range.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
