&lt;p&gt;NFL Media is seeking a seasonal photo editor to join our team for the 2026-2027 Season. The NFL’s photo department manages still imagery across our digital platforms and League groups, including editorial, social, and marketing. The ideal candidate has a passion for football and visual storytelling, and a drive to find the most engaging images for our audience. The position will primarily focus on sourcing image assets for daily news coverage, creating story-driven photo essays, and editing images incoming live from games. Other responsibilities may include assistance producing photo shoots and providing event editing support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce image assets for news stories on NFL digital platforms - source and crop thumbnails for articles and videos, produce feature art for centerpiece stories using image templates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Live edit game and tentpole images according to editorial standards: crop, tone and caption in real time. Distribute images for use across NFL ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with maintaining in-house image archive and distribution of NFL images. Ensure proper archival of incoming images from games, events, and photoshoots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide still photo coverage of NFL Media shows as needed. Shoot on set, edit and archive images.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with content for Photo department Instagram account: developing content, selecting and posting images&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with photo research projects as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-5 years experience photo editing for digital media, preferably for editorial outlets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of best practices for editorial images. Experience captioning and applying metadata to editorial standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree with emphasis in photography, visual design, or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in Adobe Photoshop and Photo Mechanic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available to work evenings and weekends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in sports photography preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with content management systems and FTP clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with photography rights and licensing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in live event coverage a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Key Attributes / Characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multitask, prioritize workload, and meet tight deadlines while maintaining quality and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for the NFL, familiarity with NFL news and storylines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potential for travel during tentpole events as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Terms / Expected Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have weekend availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7-month employment period&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
