&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview /Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Production Coordinator (Level 2) oversees the full logistics of assigned on‑location shoots for NFL Films Productions.&amp;nbsp; This role manages crew movements, equipment rentals, travel, permitting, and vendor communication from preproduction through wrap. The coordinator ensures all operational details are executed accurately and efficiently, serving as a key liaison between internal departments to keep shoots running smoothly and on schedule.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 7-month seasonal position.&amp;nbsp; Candidates are required to work 5 days week from our offices in Mt. Laurel, NJ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all logistics of on location shoots as assigned, from start to finish, specifically crew movements, equipment shipments, and vendor communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire camera, audio &amp;amp; support crew for on location filming &amp;amp; ensure the onboarding process is complete prior to filming&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate all crew travel, including booking flights, hotels &amp;amp; rental vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research &amp;amp; book local equipment rentals not provided by the NFL Films Camera &amp;amp; Audio departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research &amp;amp; book locations, oversee permitting &amp;amp; handle all administrative tasks associated with those responsibilities including securing vendor paperwork, releases &amp;amp; processing payment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle all shoot communication including updating the online shoot schedule, sending shoot emails &amp;amp; creating call sheets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with other departments to ensure budget considerations &amp;amp; crew assignments are communicated quickly &amp;amp; efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrative tasks may include answering phones, requesting certificates of insurance, reviewing invoices &amp;amp; updating department tracking documents to ensure consistency &amp;amp; accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate should have 2–3 years of experience coordinating on‑location shoots in film, television, or live event production, with demonstrated ability to independently manage logistics, travel, vendors, and shoot communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of TV/film production, including camera, audio, lighting, and grip equipment, as well as a clear understanding of crew roles, responsibilities, and on‑set workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with NFL and NFL Films programming, past and present, with the ability to support shoots that require historical context, archival awareness, or football specific operational needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Key Attributes / Characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess strong organizational and time management skills and high-level attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment and handling multiple projects simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Demands&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Position involves coordinating productions on location – candidate should be comfortable being on their feet for long periods of time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shoot &amp;amp;/or event needs may require the coordinator to travel on location up to 30% of the time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$2000/week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Terms / Expected Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Summary/Objective:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seeking football enthusiasts with outstanding work ethic and strong attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities include but are not limited to cataloging NFL Films footage into company database for archival purposes.&amp;nbsp; Loggers are asked to research significant game events to assist their assignments and perform quality control checks to ensure accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;College degree preferred with a concentration in film/television production.&amp;nbsp; Applicants should have basic computer skills and possess stout football knowledge.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;MUST&lt;/u&gt; be able to identify players, coaches, and personnel from the mid/late 1990s to 2026 and have familiarity with football terminology.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Work schedule&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
